  "prompt": "I lost my prescription slip for norco 10-325 before having filled it what can I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you've lost your prescription for Norco 10-325. Here's what you can do:\n\n1. **Contact Your Prescribing Doctor:** Reach out to the healthcare provider who prescribed Norco. Inform them about the lost prescription, and they can issue a new one for you.\n\n2. **Inform Your Pharmacy:** Let your pharmacy know about the situation. If your prescription was sent electronically, they might be able to retrieve it without needing a new slip.\n\n3. **Check for Electronic Records:** If you have access to an online patient portal or electronic health records, you might be able to view and print your prescription information there.\n\n4. **Secure Your Prescriptions:** For future reference, consider keeping a digital copy or a secure record of your prescriptions to avoid similar issues.\n\nAlways handle prescription medications responsibly and consult with your healthcare provider if you have any concerns or need assistance.",
